The paper presents a new type of LSTM unit that enables learning of hierarchical representations through multiple stages of temporal abstractions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also mentions performance on pixel-by-pixel MNIST digit classification and natural language inference tasks, indicating that it may also be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
